<div class="auxiliary-line">

            <h1>Continuity Claim Layer</h1>

            <p>VCDesign is not a function that directly controls the system.<br>
                This layer is a protocol for defining the <strong>Status</strong> where the system can claim that "Value
                is Continuous (Value Continuous)".</p>

            <h2>The Final Guard</h2>

            <blockquote>
                <p><strong>This structure never improves value.</strong><br>
                    <strong>It only prevents claiming continuity when value has already drifted.</strong>
                </p>
            </blockquote>

            <p>You must not bring any expectations of "productivity improvement" or "efficiency" into this layer.<br>
                This defines when the signboard (Claim) that the system is VCDesign compliant should be revoked.</p>

            <h2>The Claim</h2>

            <p>The system can claim to be "VCDesign compliant" only while all three of the following elements are
                functioning:</p>

            <ol>
                <li>
                    <strong>The Core (Logic to Protect)</strong><br>
                    In-design value (Constitution, BOA, Closure of Responsibility) is protected.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>The Sensor (Context Drift Sensor)</strong><br>
                    Sensors that detect changes in premises or context drift (Drift) are operating and are not being
                    ignored.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>The Loop (Judgment Return Cycle)</strong><br>
                    A cycle that stops the system or returns it to design upon detection is functioning.
                </li>
            </ol>

            <p>When even one of these is missing, the system may continue to move, but the assertion of
                <strong>"Continuity" immediately becomes void (INVALID)</strong>.</p>

            <h2>The Mechanism (Judgment Logic)</h2>

            <p>This layer monitors the following signal transitions and determines the status.</p>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Sensor State</th>
                        <th>Loop Action</th>
                        <th>Claim Status</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Normal</td>
                        <td>(Monitoring)</td>
                        <td><strong>VALID</strong></td>
                        <td>Operating normally.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Drift Detected</strong></td>
                        <td><strong>No Action / Ignored</strong></td>
                        <td><strong style="color: #F87171;">INVALID</strong></td>
                        <td>Warning was ignored. No longer VCDesign.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td><strong>Drift Detected</strong></td>
                        <td><strong>Returned / Stopped</strong></td>
                        <td><strong>VALID (Maintaining)</strong></td>
                        <td>Because it stopped/returned to protect value, the VCDesign status is maintained.</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

            <p>"Stopping" is not a failure.<br>
                Only "running out of control without stopping" means the loss of Claim.</p>

