            <h1>VCDesign Constitution</h1>

            <p>This constitution exists for<br>
                systems that have reached the point where they need it,<br>
                and yet continue to change,<br>
                and for those who intend to make them change.</p>

            <p>We consider this to be<br>
                one of the correct answers.</p>

            <h2>Phase 0：The Era Without a Constitution</h2>

            <p>Not all systems<br>
                have a constitution from the start.</p>

            <p>At this stage,<br>
                judgments were not explicitly defined,<br>
                and responsibility was taken outside the structure.</p>

            <p>Every design was a correct answer,<br>
                success was measured only by results,<br>
                and continuity was sustained by human burden.</p>

            <p>The absence of a constitution was<br>
                a premise, not a lack,<br>
                and yet the system moved.</p>

            <h2>Phase 1：Constitution for Exploration</h2>

            <p>However,<br>
                we cannot continue to measure everything by results alone.</p>

            <p>As the speed of change increased<br>
                and the number of attempts multiplied,<br>
                results appeared with delay,<br>
                and failures were repeated.</p>

            <p>At this stage,<br>
                the system began to be designed<br>
                with exploration itself as a premise for the first time.</p>

            <p>To maximize output.<br>
                To accept change without fear.<br>
                To tolerate waste.</p>

            <p>And thus,<br>
                it came to have a constitution for moving forward.</p>

            <h2>Phase 2：The Era of Transition and Mixture</h2>

            <p>A constitution for moving forward<br>
                is not always sufficient.</p>

            <p>Explorations overlap,<br>
                and the system increases in complexity.</p>

            <p>At this stage,<br>
                boundaries were set for some judgments,<br>
                while other judgments<br>
                were still left to exploration.</p>

            <p>Boundaries existed,<br>
                but they were not comprehensive,<br>
                and judgments coexisted while being fragmented.</p>

            <p>As the force of time<br>
                continued to place new boundaries,<br>
                human involvement did not decrease,<br>
                but rather had to lend its strength to new explorations.</p>

            <p>The system continued to move,<br>
                but each judgment<br>
                required a different constitution.</p>

            <h2>Phase 3：VCDesign / VCD</h2>

            <p>We cannot leave judgment<br>
                fragmented any longer.</p>

            <p>Let us design<br>
                the judgment itself.</p>

            <p>It is not<br>
                to speed up exploration.<br>
                Nor is it to stop optimization.</p>

            <p><strong>It is to ensure that the time in which value is exerted,<br>
                    is severed no longer</strong>.</p>

            <p>Judgment is<br>
                the locus of responsibility,<br>
                the thought of people,<br>
                and the act of passing on the value<br>
                that is the reason for the system's existence<br>
                to what comes next.</p>

            <p>Here,<br>
                we design the behavior of people and systems.</p>

            <hr>

            <h2>Constitution Compatibility Matrix</h2>

            <p>Flag raised on: 2026-01-15<br>
                This document records incompatibilities observed at this point in time.<br>
                It is not a prediction, recommendation, or moral judgment.</p>

            <h3>🏳️ Constitution Compatibility Matrix</h3>

            <table>
                <thead>
                    <tr>
                        <th>VCDesign × Constitution</th>
                        <th>Compatibility</th>
                        <th>One-line Reason</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <td>VCDesign × Engagement Maximization</td>
                        <td>❌ No</td>
                        <td>Infinite engagement conflicts with decision closure and human autonomy.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>VCDesign × e/acc (Accelerationism)</td>
                        <td>❌ No</td>
                        <td>Forced acceleration breaks value continuity across time.</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>VCDesign × Cost-Cutter</td>
                        <td>⚠️ Conditional</td>
                        <td>Cost optimization is acceptable only while preserving human decision margin.</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>

